OL,3,CHow the Golders Green terror attack
OL,4,Cunfolded
OL,6,FCounter terrorism police investigating
OL,7,Fthe attack have said they believe the
OL,8,Fsuspect was connected to an
OL,9,F"altercation" with another person in
OL,10,Fsouth-east London, a few hours before
OL,11,Fthe attack.
OL,13,FThe Met said officers were called to
OL,14,Fan address in Great Dover Street,
OL,15,FSouthwark, at around 8.50am, after a
OL,16,Fman armed with a knife was believed to
OL,17,Fhave had an altercation with the
OL,18,Foccupant before leaving.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1777583466
OL,3,CHow the Golders Green terror attack
OL,4,Cunfolded
OL,6,FThe occupant suffered minor injuries,
OL,7,Fbut the suspect was not found, and
OL,8,Fofficers believe he is the same man
OL,9,Farrested in Golders Green.
OL,11,FFirst attack carried out on Highfield
OL,12,FAvenue
OL,14,FBy 11am, the suspect had travelled
OL,15,Froughly 10 miles to Golders Green and
OL,16,F15 mintues later, he allegedly carried
OL,17,Fout the first attack on Highfield
OL,18,FAvenue, near Golders Green Road.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
